-- Peru Stocks: El Brocal, Rio Alto, Scotiabank, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2011-12-22T21:26:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/peru-stocks-el-brocal-rio-alto-scotiabank-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.1 percent to 19,383.07. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index  climbed 0.5 percent to 2,515.62.  Copper miners gained as futures advanced for a third day in
 New York .  Southern Copper Corp.  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper
producer, rose 2.5 percent to $30.55.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal
SAA  (BROCALC1 PE), a copper and zinc producer, climbed 1.9
percent to 45.87 soles.  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA  (CVERDEC1
PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., gained 1
percent to $35.85 after the company signed a three-year labor
accord with workers.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian company with a
mine in Peru, declined 1.6 percent to $3.12 after gold declined
for the third day in four in New York, said  Daniel Romero , an
analyst at Lima-based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Scotiabank Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1 PE), the local unit of
 Canada ’s third-largest bank, declined 1.3 percent to 37.50 soles
after Peru’s banking regulator said it aims to cut lending
interest rates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
